'''''Stenotrema''''' is a genus of [[gastropod]] in the family [[Polygyridae]]. These are typically small to medium snails, with a velvety or hairy surface and a narrow [[aperture (mollusc)|aperture]], usually closely guarded by well-developed "teeth".

== Distribution ==
The genus occurs throughout most of North America, from Alaska, though Canada and the United States, into Mexico.<ref name="Pilsbry1940">Pilsbry, Henry A. 1940. ''Land Mollusca of North America (North of Mexico)''. Acad. Nat. Sci. Philadelphia,  Monograph 3, vol. 1(2): 639-688.</ref>

